#!/usr/bin/env tape
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# .tape v1.2 — grammar primer (cold-read by any LLM / agent / human)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Form: each entry is `@<type> <id> := "<subject>" :: <kind> [<grades>]`
#       optionally followed by body lines (2-space indent) — key=value,
#       edges (<- -> => …), or quoted prose.
#
# ENTRY TYPES (17):
#   Runtime (10): @S session  @U user  @A assistant  @T tool-call  @R result
#                 @H hook  @D decision  @K cost  @P provider  @? anomaly
#   Foundation:   @I identity-claim
#   Declarative:  @X external-citation  @F forbidden-pattern  @N note
#                 @C config  @L layout  @V spec-version
#
# EDGES (12, on body lines, 2-space indent):
#   Causal:     <- caused-by   -> triggers   == continues
#               ~> supersedes  !! aborts     |> verified-by
#   Effect:     => produces (followed by quoted natural-language)
#   Structural: <: specializes  :> generalizes  ?> soft-depends
#               !> conflicts-with  @> projects-to (e.g. @> AGENTS.md)
#
# GRADE TAGS (in [...] on entry header):
#   Delivery:   ok · err · denied · cancelled · partial · superseded
#   Governance: required · recommended · optional · draft · active · deprecated
#   Scoped:     allow:<x> · deny:<x>
#   Time/index: T<n> (turn)  N<n> (wall-sec)  d=<YYYY-MM-DD>
#
# PAYLOAD SYNTAX (body lines):
#   key = "value"           single-line string
#   key = [a, b, c]         array literal
#   key <<~EOF              heredoc (multi-line; ends with EOF on own line)
#     multi-line text
#   EOF
#   "see [@x1] §3"          inline citation by entry id
#   `cmd or path`           backtick code-span (inline only)
#
# Full spec: ~/core/tape/spec/tape.md (or github.com/dancinlab/tape)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════


# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# CRISPR-CAS13-POC-DIAGNOSTIC.log.tape — append-only event history (v1.2 split)
# Sibling: CRISPR-CAS13-POC-DIAGNOSTIC.tape (architecture-current, editable)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

@V := "tape" :: spec [active]
  version = "1.2"

# §Log — entries chronological, oldest first.

@A rewrite := "CRISPR-CAS13-POC-DIAGNOSTIC.tape rewritten from lattice-tautology stub to real-science SSOT" :: rewrite [ok d=2026-05-16]
  origin = "CRISPR-CAS13-POC-DIAGNOSTIC.tape was a fabricated lattice-tautology stub (created in the hexa-bio mass-split, commit 153b5a2). Approximately 90 @D `row_*` / `b_*` entries asserted CRISPR-diagnostic facts (LoD, TTR, cost per test, shelf life, capital cost, BOM cassette weights, vendor lists, mk1→mk2 roadmap, banner ASCII-art and an 'alien-grade 10' product-maturity claim) as DERIVATIONS from the n=6 lattice and as physical-limit-anchored MVP claims that did not distinguish RESEARCH demonstrations from FDA-CLEARED / IVDR-CERTIFIED products. Every `row_*` / `b_*` stub plus the banner ASCII-art comments deleted."
  authored = "Hand-written with real CRISPR-diagnostics science. Replaces the stub with: §1 what CRISPR-Dx is (Cas13/Cas12 collateral-cleavage POC diagnostic; Cas-biology cross-link to CRISPR-GENE-EDITING.tape, not re-derived); §2 effector families & platforms (Cas13 / Cas12a mechanism rows + SHERLOCK / DETECTR / STOPCovid / SHINE platform rows — each |>-grounded to the named landmark paper); §3 detection chemistry (isothermal pre-amplification RPA / LAMP; fluorescent / LFA / electrochemical / multiplex readouts); §3b head-to-head comparison vs NAAT-PCR / antigen-LFA / sequencing (6 @D :: comparison rows: cmp_axis / naat_pcr / crispr_dx / antigen_lfa / sequencing / synthesis — qualitative analyte / LoD / TTR / instrument / multiplex / signature-limit rows); §4 SIX @D :: real-limit anchors (clinical-validation gap research-to-cleared HARD WALL · cold-chain & reagent stability HARD WALL · manufacturing scale & cost vs antigen LFA ECONOMIC WALL · off-target / specificity floor at low template copies SOFT WALL · regulatory pathway IVDR/FDA HARD WALL · sample-prep bottleneck BIOLOGICAL/ENGINEERING WALL); §5 @F f_lattice_fit + @N n6_honest_stance (governance + honest n=6 declination); §6 three falsifiable predictions with explicit falsifiers + sources (pre-amplification necessary for clinical-LoD; clinical-validation-gap multi-year; one-pot improves field-deployability); §7 cross-links to CRISPR-GENE-EDITING.tape (Cas biology) + MEDICAL-DEVICE.tape (regulatory pathway, NOT duplicated here) + hexa-bio AGENTS.tape (governance); §8 twelve real @X :: literature citations."
  research-vs-cleared = "EXPLICIT discipline throughout: scope_disclaimer note + lim_clinical_validation_gap real-limit + tp_2 prediction all state the same gap — almost the entire CRISPR-Dx literature is ANALYTICAL (LoD on contrived + small clinical panels vs NAAT reference); the path to an FDA-cleared / CE-IVDR product requires multi-year prospective clinical-performance studies, manufacturing / stability programs, human-factors validation, regulatory submission and PMS. Most publicly-known CRISPR-Dx clearances arose under pandemic-era Emergency Use Authorisation — a SPECIAL TIME-LIMITED pathway, NOT a standard premarket clearance. A 'CRISPR-Dx for X' paper is not the same kind of object as an 'FDA-cleared CRISPR-Dx for X' kit; conflating them is the central honesty failure this rewrite exists to prevent. The lim_regulatory_pathway anchor cross-links to MEDICAL-DEVICE.tape rather than restating its IVDR / FDA mechanics here, mirroring the cohort SSOT-deference discipline (hexa-bio AGENTS.tape g5_sister_repo_cli at the tape-level analogue)."
  n6-stance = "Declined as a derivation tool. @F f_lattice_fit (lattice-fit-on-crispr-diagnostics, deny:write) + @N n6_honest_stance state plainly: CRISPR-Dx exposes NO natural n=6 invariant — Cas effector taxonomy, spacer/guide lengths, SHERLOCKv2 4-channel multiplex (set by ortholog availability + LFA-line spatial resolution, NOT τ=4), RPA ~10^9 / ~20 min amplification (enzymology, NOT σ-derived), LFA visual LoD (Au-NP plasmon optics + nitrocellulose capillarity, NOT φ), and target-specific TTR/LoD/cost are empirically MEASURED in landmark papers. Any σ/τ/φ/J₂ numeric coincidence is OBSERVATION ONLY."
  governance = "Complies with hexa-bio AGENTS.tape g1 (real-limits-first — 6 real-limit anchors), g2 (lattice-is-tool — declined as derivation), g3 (honesty-obligation-external — no lattice-fit on FDA / EU IVDR / WHO / ISO), g8 (in-silico-only-claim-scope — @N scope_disclaimer added; NOT clinical / regulatory / laboratory-protocol guidance; clinical-validation gap explicit), f1 (no lattice-fit on external regulators / standards bodies), f2 (no in-silico → clinical / regulatory claim — pandemic-era EUAs are explicitly NOT generic CRISPR-Dx-platform clearance). Provenance recorded in @I id001 rewritten-from key. Cross-link to MEDICAL-DEVICE.tape avoids duplication of the regulatory-pathway material and respects the cohort SSOT-deference discipline."
  honesty-caveats = "No fabricated numbers / citations. Confident references (full author lists + journal + year + volume): Abudayyeh 2016 Science 353:aaf5573 (Cas13/C2c2); Chen 2018 Science 360:436–439 (DETECTR / Cas12a); Gootenberg 2017 Science 356:438–442 (SHERLOCKv1); Gootenberg 2018 Science 360:439–444 (SHERLOCKv2 multiplex); Myhrvold 2018 Science 360:444–448 (HUDSON); Joung 2020 NEJM 383:1492–1494 (STOPCovid); Broughton 2020 Nat Biotechnol 38:870–874 (DETECTR-LFA SARS-CoV-2); Piepenburg 2006 PLoS Biol 4:e204 (RPA); Notomi 2000 Nucleic Acids Res 28:e63 (LAMP); EU IVDR Regulation (EU) 2017/746 (IVDR date-of-application 26 May 2022). Primary-author/era-flagged (exact volume not asserted): Arizti-Sanz et al. (SHINE) — Nat Commun era 2020/2022 ('exact volume not asserted'). Three @X :: sibling-tape / governance entries cross-link to CRISPR-GENE-EDITING.tape, MEDICAL-DEVICE.tape, hexa-bio AGENTS.tape — these are repo-internal SSOT cross-links, distinct from the external-literature @X entries. Specific USD-per-test, exact median EUA-to-clearance timelines, and TB / HIV-specific clinical-sensitivity figures are deliberately NOT asserted; the cost / timeline / clinical-sensitivity gaps are cited as program-class observations only ([@lim_manufacturing_cost] / [@lim_clinical_validation_gap])."
  lint = "python3 selftest/tape_lattice_honesty_lint.py CRISPR-CAS13-POC-DIAGNOSTIC.tape --json → {\"verdict\": \"PASS\", \"deriv_warnings\": [], \"has_guard\": true, \"has_stance\": true, \"grounded\": true} · __TAPE_LATTICE_HONESTY__ PASS · zero lattice-derivation lines remain · every row_* / b_* stub / banner ASCII-art deleted · top v1.2 grammar primer + banner + @V :: spec version=1.2 preserved verbatim."
